2 = 93 | goals2 = 10\n| years3 = 2018\u2013     | clubs3 = [[Str\u00f8msgodset Toppfotball|Str\u00f8msgodset]]    | caps3 =  54 | goals3 =  2\n| nationalyears1 = 2010 |nationalteam1 = Norway U15 |nationalcaps1 = 5 |nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2 = 2011 |nationalteam2 = Norway U16 |nationalcaps2 = 12 |nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2012 |nationalteam3 = [[Norway national under-17 football team|Norway U17]] |nationalcaps3 = 6 |nationalgoals3 = 2\n| club-update = 24 November 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 5 June 2013\n}}\n\n'''Herman S\u00f8rby Stengel''' (born 26 August 1995) is a Norwegian [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Eliteserien]] side [[Str\u00f8msgodset Toppfotball|Str\u00f8msgodset]]. He has previously played for [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]] and [[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerenga]], and has represented his country at youth level.\n\n==Club career==\n\nStengel was born in [[L\u00f8renskog]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=246687 |language=Norwegian |title=Herman Stengel |work=altomfotball.no |accessdate=4 January 2013}}</ref> and grew up in [[Hokksund]], where he played for [[Hokksund IL|Hokksund]] before he joined [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]] as a youth. He started playing for their senior B team, [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball 2|Stab\u00e6k 2]], and became the youngest goalscorer ever in the [[Norwegian Second Division]]. In May 2010 he scored his first senior goal at the age 14 years and 261 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bygdeposten.no/Sport/article5127837.ece|title=Tidenes yngste m\u00e5lscorer|date=23 May 2010|newspaper=[[Bygdeposten]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2 October 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Stengel did a trial at [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] together with [[Mats M\u00f8ller D\u00e6hli]], who later joined the club's academy and [[Sondre Tronstad]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Youngster impresses United|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11667_5692975,00.html|publisher=Sky Sports |first=Kent |last=Hedlundh |date=13 November 2009 |accessdate=4 June 2013}}</ref> In December 2012, Stab\u00e6k granted Stengel a week to trial with [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Herman Stengel skal trene med PSV |language=Norwegian |url=http://www.stabak.no/latest-news/article/1oh1beifvg82m1e9w1k9usgj7f/title/herman-stengel-skal-trene-med-psv |publisher=Stab\u00e6k Fotball |first=Mads |last=Andreassen |date=5 December 2012 |accessdate=4 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140521110137/http://www.stabak.no/latest-news/article/1oh1beifvg82m1e9w1k9usgj7f/title/herman-stengel-skal-trene-med-psv |archivedate=21 May 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 2 October 2011, Stengel made his [[Norwegian Premier League]] debut, starting the match against [[Sarpsborg 08]]. Aged 16 years and 37 days, he became the youngest Stab\u00e6k-player to start a match in Tippeligaen, and the then third youngest player in the Norwegian top division.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.budstikka.no/sport/stab%C3%A6k/tidenes-yngste-debuterer-for-stabek-1.6528007|title=Tidenes yngste debuterer for Stab\u00e6k|last=Str\u00f8mnes|first=Andr\u00e9|date=2 October 2011|newspaper=[[Budstikka]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2 October 2011}}</ref>\n\nStengel became known during the autumn of 2011, as he was a piece of [[Veigar P\u00e1ll Gunnarsson]]'s transfer to [[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerenga]], which caused great [[Veigar P\u00e1ll Gunnarsson transfer 2011|controversy]]. [[TV 2 (Norway)]] revealed on 12 October 2011 that Gunnarsson was transferred to V\u00e5lerenga for 1 million NOK, while V\u00e5lerenga paid a transfer fee of 4 million NOK for an option for the then 15-year-old footballer Stengel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/rbk-boed-5-mill-for-gunnarsson-stabaek-solgte-til-vif-for-en-mill-3608694.html |language=Norwegian |title=\u2013 Vil bli kjent som fotballspiller |work=tv2.no |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV 2]] |date=17 February 2012 |accessdate=19 February 2012}}</ref> In February 2012, Stengel stated that he wants to be known as a footballer, not as the guy who was a piece in the controversial football transfer, and that his dream is to play in one of the best leagues in Europe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/-vil-bli-kjent-som-fotballspiller-3711915.html |language=Norwegian |title=RBK b\u00f8d 5 mill for Gunnarsson \u2013 Stab\u00e6k solgte til VIF for \u00e9n mill |work=tv2.no |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV 2]] |date=12 October 2011 |accessdate=28 November 2011}}</ref>\n\nAfter Stab\u00e6k was relegated from Tippeligaen in [[2012 Tippeligaen|2012]], Stengel was one of the key-players in the young Stab\u00e6k-team that finished the [[2013 Adeccoligaen|2013 season]] second in the [[Norwegian First Division|First Division]] and won promotion back to Tippeligaen. His contract with Stab\u00e6k expired after the season and he joined V\u00e5lerenga as a free agent ahead of the 2014 season, signing a four-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2013/12/11/sport/fotball/tippeliagen/valerenga/30787833/ |language=Norwegian |title=Herman Stengel er klar for V\u00e5lerenga |newspaper=Dagbladet |first=Tore Ulrik |last=Bratland |date=11 December 2013 |accessdate=6 January 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 Nov 2017, [[Str\u00f8msgodset Toppfotball]] announced that Stengel had signed a three-year deal from 1 Jan 2018.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.godset.no/nyheter/stengel-er-klar-for-godset |language=Norwegian |title=Stengel er klar for Godset|newspaper=|first= |last=|date=20 November 2017 |accessdate=20 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nStengel scored six goals in twenty-three matches for Norwegian under-15 to under-17 between 2010 and 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fotball.no/Community/Profil/?fiksId=2526739 |language=Norwegian |title=Herman S\u00f8rby Stengel |work=fotball.no |publisher=Football Association of Norway |accessdate=5 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022064820/http://www.fotball.no/Community/Profil/?fiksId=2526739 |archivedate=22 October 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 24 November 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Herman Stengel|url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=246687&tournamentId=1&seasonId=340&teamId=328&useFullUrl=false|website=altomfotball.no|publisher=TV 2|accessdate=2 December 2018|language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\" |[[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]\n|[[2011 Tippeligaen|2011]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[Tippeligaen]]\n|5||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||6||0\n|-\n|[[2012 Tippeligaen|2012]]\n|20||0||3||0||2||0||25||0\n|-\n|[[2013 Adeccoligaen|2013]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" |[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|29||0||4||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||33||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!54!!0!!8!!1!!2!!0!!64!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\" |[[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerenga]] \n|[[2014 Tippeligaen|2014]]\n|rowspan=\"3\" |[[Tippeligaen]]\n|24||2||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||26||2\n|-\n|[[2015 Tippeligaen|2015]]\n|23||2||2||2||colspan=\"2\"|-||25||4\n|-\n|[[2016 Tippeligaen|2016]]\n|25||0||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||29||0\n|-\n|[[2017 Eliteserien|2017]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" |[[Eliteserien]]\n|21||6||5||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||26||7\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!93!!10!!13!!3!!-!!-!!106!!3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" |[[Str\u00f8msgodset Toppfotball|Str\u00f8msgodset]]\n|[[2018 Eliteserien|2018]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[Eliteserien]]\n|25||1||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||31||1\n|-\n|[[2019 Eliteserien|2019]]\n|29||1||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||32